The noise of beauty surrounds me
I feel in peace
In line
The single file line you would stand in school
The chorus is soothing
Calm
Beautiful as the birds flying threw late spring
It gets harder. Deeper. Stronger.
That single file line gives me feelings of claustrophobic.
I shake, repeatedly. Nervously
I grab my head shaking the sickness out
My mind loses control
I burst out of the single file line and run
As I run, the calmness comes back
I'm free
Free, running tords the doors of escape
The beauty as the birds flying over my head, the cool warm air on my face
I begin to smile
My eyes tear up
My mind still free as I reach the doors of true freedom
They dont open
Locked
My heart drops
I back into a corner
I lost my sense of awareness
The walls are caving
My mind in overload
I bang on the walls
screaming for help
Freedom!
My eyes close
They open
........
Hello
Where am I?
Welcome to hell
Hell?
I get pushed off a cliff
My eyes close...
They open with tears of happiness
The air whistling past my ears
The freedom
The joy
Then the black.........
